The paper deals with image classification using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The focus on fine-grained classification and low-resolution images suggests a sub-category of cs.CV that deals with these specific challenges. Additionally, the use of deep learning techniques and end-to-end training suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of image super-resolution techniques also suggests a potential overlap with multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
